addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>E</fr:tex> be an object in a category <fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex> such that all binary cartesian products with <fr:tex>E</fr:tex> exist. We say that <fr:tex>E</fr:tex> is <fr:em>exponentiable</fr:em> when the product endofunctor <fr:tex>-\times  E</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex> has a right adjoint, which we shall write <fr:tex>E\Rightarrow- </fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks><fr:tree
